<paragraph id="9A3236A2FFBDFFDA2AD6FB1FFA6EFB4A" blockId="2.[151,1437,1088,2015]" box="[199,1416,1161,1187]" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">Etymology. The species is dedicated to the to the mother of the first author, Maria Rosalie Grangeiro Xavier.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D2976529FFBDFFDA2AD6FB3BFE86FAE6" pageId="2" pageNumber="319" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9A3236A2FFBDFFDA2AD6FB3BFE86FAE6" blockId="2.[151,1437,1088,2015]" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">Diagnosis. This species is characterized by the male terminalia: hypandrium strip-like with two small lateral setae; one pair of triangular parameres with acute apex, asymmetrical; aedeagus paired, asymmetrical, one shaft with curved apex.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D2976529FFBDFFDA2AD6FA8FFE70F87E" pageId="2" pageNumber="319" type="description">
<paragraph id="9A3236A2FFBDFFDA2AD6FA8FFE3FF89A" blockId="2.[151,1437,1088,2015]" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">
Description. Adult male. Eye bridge with three facet rows, separated at median by almost one facet diameter, interocular suture present, V-shaped, open dorsally. Two larger supraocular setae alveoli (
<figureCitation id="02B62A27FFBDFFDA2E99FAABFB3DFABE" box="[1160,1243,1341,1367]" captionStart="FIGURE 12–20" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1926,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,348,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,345,1901]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 12–20. Australopericoma xavierae sp. nov. (12) head, anterior; (13) head, posterior; (14) base of antenna: scape, pedicel and five basal flagellomeres; (15) Flagellomeres 9–14; (16) palpus; (17) wing; (18) male terminalia, ventral: epandrium, cerci, epiproct and hypoproct; (19) hypandrium, gonocoxites, gonostyli and aedeagus, dorsal; (20) gonocoxal apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3665321/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) and four or five larger alveoli on lateroposterior margin of eye (
<figureCitation id="02B62A27FFBDFFDA28BCFAF7FCE7FA92" box="[685,769,1377,1403]" captionStart="FIGURE 12–20" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1926,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,348,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,345,1901]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 12–20. Australopericoma xavierae sp. nov. (12) head, anterior; (13) head, posterior; (14) base of antenna: scape, pedicel and five basal flagellomeres; (15) Flagellomeres 9–14; (16) palpus; (17) wing; (18) male terminalia, ventral: epandrium, cerci, epiproct and hypoproct; (19) hypandrium, gonocoxites, gonostyli and aedeagus, dorsal; (20) gonocoxal apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3665321/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Antenna with scape cylindrical, 1.5 times of the spherical pedicel (
<figureCitation id="02B62A27FFBDFFDA2AE9FA13FEADFA76" box="[248,331,1413,1439]" captionStart="FIGURE 12–20" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1926,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,348,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,345,1901]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 12–20. Australopericoma xavierae sp. nov. (12) head, anterior; (13) head, posterior; (14) base of antenna: scape, pedicel and five basal flagellomeres; (15) Flagellomeres 9–14; (16) palpus; (17) wing; (18) male terminalia, ventral: epandrium, cerci, epiproct and hypoproct; (19) hypandrium, gonocoxites, gonostyli and aedeagus, dorsal; (20) gonocoxal apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3665321/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
); 14 flagellomeres; basal flagellomeres fusiform; 13th flagellomere reduced, ovoid, 14th spherical with apiculus with the same length of flagellomere; flagellomeres 3–10 with a pair of filiform ascoids, shorter than the flagellomere bearing them (
<figureCitation id="02B62A27FFBDFFDA2BE4FA5BFDAEFA0E" box="[501,584,1484,1511]" captionStart="FIGURE 12–20" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1926,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,348,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,345,1901]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 12–20. Australopericoma xavierae sp. nov. (12) head, anterior; (13) head, posterior; (14) base of antenna: scape, pedicel and five basal flagellomeres; (15) Flagellomeres 9–14; (16) palpus; (17) wing; (18) male terminalia, ventral: epandrium, cerci, epiproct and hypoproct; (19) hypandrium, gonocoxites, gonostyli and aedeagus, dorsal; (20) gonocoxal apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3665321/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Mouthparts extending to the tip of the basal palpus segment, labellum with apicolateral bristles (
<figureCitation id="02B62A27FFBDFFDA2B92FA67FDE8F9E2" box="[387,526,1521,1547]" captionStart="FIGURE 12–20" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1926,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,348,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,345,1901]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 12–20. Australopericoma xavierae sp. nov. (12) head, anterior; (13) head, posterior; (14) base of antenna: scape, pedicel and five basal flagellomeres; (15) Flagellomeres 9–14; (16) palpus; (17) wing; (18) male terminalia, ventral: epandrium, cerci, epiproct and hypoproct; (19) hypandrium, gonocoxites, gonostyli and aedeagus, dorsal; (20) gonocoxal apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3665321/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">Figs. 12, 13</figureCitation>
). Palpus formula = 1:1.8:1.8:2.5, all segments striated (
<figureCitation id="02B62A27FFBDFFDA2E92FA67FB31F9E5" box="[1155,1239,1521,1548]" captionStart="FIGURE 12–20" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1926,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,348,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,345,1901]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 12–20. Australopericoma xavierae sp. nov. (12) head, anterior; (13) head, posterior; (14) base of antenna: scape, pedicel and five basal flagellomeres; (15) Flagellomeres 9–14; (16) palpus; (17) wing; (18) male terminalia, ventral: epandrium, cerci, epiproct and hypoproct; (19) hypandrium, gonocoxites, gonostyli and aedeagus, dorsal; (20) gonocoxal apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3665321/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Wing (
<figureCitation id="02B62A27FFBDFFDA2F2BFA67FA68F9E2" box="[1338,1422,1521,1547]" captionStart="FIGURE 12–20" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1926,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,348,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,345,1901]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 12–20. Australopericoma xavierae sp. nov. (12) head, anterior; (13) head, posterior; (14) base of antenna: scape, pedicel and five basal flagellomeres; (15) Flagellomeres 9–14; (16) palpus; (17) wing; (18) male terminalia, ventral: epandrium, cerci, epiproct and hypoproct; (19) hypandrium, gonocoxites, gonostyli and aedeagus, dorsal; (20) gonocoxal apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3665321/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
): radial fork at the same level of medial fork, radial and medial forks arising basal to apex of CuA 
<subScript id="060934E7FFBDFFDA2ED0F9B0FB2FF9DD" attach="left" box="[1217,1225,1574,1588]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">2</subScript>
; R 
<subScript id="060934E7FFBDFFDA2EFBF9B0FB14F9DD" attach="left" box="[1258,1266,1574,1588]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">5</subScript>
ending slightly beyond of wing tip. Male terminalia (in dorsoventral view): epandrium plate-like, rectangular, longer than wide, distal margin concave, with apical pilosity; presence of two foramina near proximal margin. Cercus long, two times the length of epandrium, with one apical tenaculum. Epiproct subtriangular microsetose at apex. Hypoproct rounded at apex with apical micropilosity (
<figureCitation id="02B62A27FFBDFFDA2806F933FD8DF956" box="[535,619,1701,1727]" captionStart="FIGURE 12–20" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1926,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,348,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,345,1901]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 12–20. Australopericoma xavierae sp. nov. (12) head, anterior; (13) head, posterior; (14) base of antenna: scape, pedicel and five basal flagellomeres; (15) Flagellomeres 9–14; (16) palpus; (17) wing; (18) male terminalia, ventral: epandrium, cerci, epiproct and hypoproct; (19) hypandrium, gonocoxites, gonostyli and aedeagus, dorsal; (20) gonocoxal apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3665321/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium strip-like with four smaller setae alveoli, one pair on each side. Gonocoxite robust basally larger than apex, pilose, approximately the same length as gonostylus. Gonostylus slightly curved, pilose, base wider than apex and ending in in a pointed apex (
<figureCitation id="02B62A27FFBDFFDA2E16F97BFBBDF8EE" box="[1031,1115,1773,1799]" captionStart="FIGURE 12–20" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1926,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,348,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,345,1901]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 12–20. Australopericoma xavierae sp. nov. (12) head, anterior; (13) head, posterior; (14) base of antenna: scape, pedicel and five basal flagellomeres; (15) Flagellomeres 9–14; (16) palpus; (17) wing; (18) male terminalia, ventral: epandrium, cerci, epiproct and hypoproct; (19) hypandrium, gonocoxites, gonostyli and aedeagus, dorsal; (20) gonocoxal apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3665321/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxal apodeme fused anteriorly and bilobed posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="02B62A27FFBDFFDA280AF887FD89F8C2" box="[539,623,1809,1835]" captionStart="FIGURE 12–20" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1926,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,348,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,345,1901]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 12–20. Australopericoma xavierae sp. nov. (12) head, anterior; (13) head, posterior; (14) base of antenna: scape, pedicel and five basal flagellomeres; (15) Flagellomeres 9–14; (16) palpus; (17) wing; (18) male terminalia, ventral: epandrium, cerci, epiproct and hypoproct; (19) hypandrium, gonocoxites, gonostyli and aedeagus, dorsal; (20) gonocoxal apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3665321/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus paired, asymmetrical, one side with apex curved. Ejaculatory apodeme almost as long as aedeagus. One pair of parameres asymmetrical, triangular, with acute apex, one third the length of aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="02B62A27FFBDFFDA2B69F8CFFE2AF89A" box="[376,460,1881,1907]" captionStart="FIGURE 12–20" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1926,1951]" captionTargetBox="[179,1420,348,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,345,1901]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 12–20. Australopericoma xavierae sp. nov. (12) head, anterior; (13) head, posterior; (14) base of antenna: scape, pedicel and five basal flagellomeres; (15) Flagellomeres 9–14; (16) palpus; (17) wing; (18) male terminalia, ventral: epandrium, cerci, epiproct and hypoproct; (19) hypandrium, gonocoxites, gonostyli and aedeagus, dorsal; (20) gonocoxal apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3665321/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
