<subSubSection id="D2976529FFBDFFDB2AD6F853FF22FEAA" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="320" pageId="2" pageNumber="319" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9A3236A2FFBDFFDB2AD6F853FF22FEAA" blockId="2.[151,1437,1088,2015]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,153,323]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="320" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">
Comments. Three species of 
<taxonomicName id="5D8D4D21FFBDFFDA2804F853FD39F836" authorityName="Vaillant" authorityYear="1975" box="[533,735,1989,2015]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Australopericoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A8F9EAB0FFBDFFDA2804F853FD39F836" box="[533,735,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">Australopericoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have robust gonocoxites, 
<emphasis id="A8F9EAB0FFBDFFDA2E1AF850FBC8F836" box="[1035,1070,1990,2015]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="319">i.e.</emphasis>
they are broader than long, and short parameres: the two new species 
<taxonomicName id="5D8D4D21FFBCFFDB2859FF0FFD5EFF5A" authority="Araújo &amp; Bravo, 2020" authorityName="Araújo &amp; Bravo" authorityYear="2020" box="[584,696,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Australopericoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="onofrei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="A8F9EAB0FFBCFFDB2859FF0FFD5EFF5A" box="[584,696,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">A. onofrei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="B3CA57CBFFBCFFDB28D1FF0FFCFCFF5A" box="[704,794,153,179]" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5D8D4D21FFBCFFDB2936FF0FFC41FF5A" authority="Araújo &amp; Bravo, 2020" authorityName="Araújo &amp; Bravo" authorityYear="2020" box="[807,935,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Australopericoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xavierae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="A8F9EAB0FFBCFFDB2936FF0FFC41FF5A" box="[807,935,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">A. xavierae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="B3CA57CBFFBCFFDB29A1FF0FFBEEFF5A" box="[944,1032,153,179]" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="5D8D4D21FFBCFFDB2E51FF0FFADBFF5D" authority="(Tonnoir)" baseAuthorityName="Tonnoir" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[1088,1341,153,180]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Australopericoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidula">
<emphasis id="A8F9EAB0FFBCFFDB2E51FF0FFB20FF5A" box="[1088,1222,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">A. pallidula</emphasis>
(Tonnoir)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="5D8D4D21FFBCFFDB2F59FF0FFF5BFF3E" authority="Araújo &amp; Bravo, 2020" authorityName="Araújo &amp; Bravo" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Australopericoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="onofrei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="A8F9EAB0FFBCFFDB2F59FF0FFF5BFF3E" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">A. onofrei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="B3CA57CBFFBCFFDB2AD4FF2BFEFAFF3E" box="[197,284,189,215]" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="5D8D4D21FFBCFFDB2BA3FF2BFDD7FF3E" authorityName="Araújo &amp; Bravo" authorityYear="2020" box="[434,561,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Australopericoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xavierae">
<emphasis id="A8F9EAB0FFBCFFDB2BA3FF2BFDD7FF3E" box="[434,561,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">A. xavierae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5D8D4D21FFBCFFDB2851FF2BFD23FF3E" baseAuthorityName="Tonnoir" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[576,709,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Australopericoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidula">
<emphasis id="A8F9EAB0FFBCFFDB2851FF2BFD23FF3E" box="[576,709,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">A. pallidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and all other species of 
<taxonomicName id="5D8D4D21FFBCFFDB29CBFF2BFB42FF3E" authorityName="Vaillant" authorityYear="1975" box="[986,1188,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Australopericoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A8F9EAB0FFBCFFDB29CBFF2BFB42FF3E" box="[986,1188,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">Australopericoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of an unsclerotized dorsal area between the parameres. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName id="5D8D4D21FFBCFFDB2973FF77FC07FF12" authorityName="Araújo &amp; Bravo" authorityYear="2020" box="[866,993,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Australopericoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xavierae">
<emphasis id="A8F9EAB0FFBCFFDB2973FF77FC07FF12" box="[866,993,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">A. xavierae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="5D8D4D21FFBCFFDB2E69FF77FB1AFF12" baseAuthorityName="Tonnoir" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[1144,1276,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Australopericoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidula">
<emphasis id="A8F9EAB0FFBCFFDB2E69FF77FB1AFF12" box="[1144,1276,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">A. pallidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the size of ejaculatory apodeme, longer than aedeagus in the new species, very short in 
<taxonomicName id="5D8D4D21FFBCFFDB2E11FE93FF26FEAA" authority="(Quate &amp; Brown, 2004: 94)" baseAuthorityName="Quate &amp; Brown" baseAuthorityPageNumber="94" baseAuthorityYear="2004" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Australopericoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidula">
<emphasis id="A8F9EAB0FFBCFFDB2E11FE93FB60FEF6" box="[1024,1158,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">A. pallidula</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="FE1C4B53FFBCFFDB2E87FE93FF51FEAA" author="Quate, L. W. &amp; Brown, B. V." pageId="3" pageNumber="320" pagination="1 - 117" refId="ref2517" refString="Quate, L. W. &amp; Brown, B. V. (2004) Revision of Neotropical Setomimini (Diptera: Psychodidae: Psychodinae). Contributions in Science Natural History Museum of Los Angeles, 500, 1 - 117." type="journal article" year="2004">Quate &amp; Brown, 2004: 94</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
